ShutDown /S and press Enter. The system will perform an orderly shutdown after 30 seconds.

ShutDown /S /M \\RemoteComputer  If you want to shut down a remote system.

ShutDown /S /T:0   The /T the shutdown—a value of 0 means that the shutdown is immediate.

ShutDown /R  shutdown and restart

ShutDown /G  restore the Windows applications that were open at the time of the shutdown.

